factorial(54)/(factorial(6)*factorial(48))
25827165/(49^6)
The probability of one of the numbers matching a drawn number is $\frac{1}{49}$. In addition, the numbers are being drawn without replacement and their order does not matter, so the number of possible winning combinations is:
$$
\begin{array}{rcl}
\binom{49 + 6 - 1}{6} & = & \binom{54}{6}\\
& = &  \frac{54!}{6!(54-6)!}\\
& = &  \frac{54!}{6!48!}\\
& = & 25827165
\end{array}
$$
$\therefore p = \frac{25827165}{49^6} \approx 0.0019$
